section.section:
For purposes of this subsection, "displaced homemaker" is an individual who:
Is 30 years of age or older;
Has worked for the family in the family home;
Is not gainfully employed;
Has had, or would have, difficulty finding employment;
Has depended on the income of a family member and has lost that income as the result of separation, divorce, or the death or disability of that family member; or
Has depended on government assistance as the parent of dependent children and is no longer eligible for such assistance; and
Has an annual income that does not exceed:
The federal Office of Management and Budget poverty income guidelines; or
The United States Department of Labor, Bureau of Labor Statistics, 70 percent lower living standard income level.
